reviews.title: That was once but never again!
reviews.text: Price - quality ratio downright poor . One mistake on the bill can happen - but no excuse. That was really the last time

reviews.title: Very Good Service and Very Good Food!
reviews.text:
Cozy location, nice view!
Good and Fast Service and Very Good Food!

Both fish and also the mix grill an absolute must!

reviews.title: Be careful rip-off!
reviews.text:
Beware tourist trap! I've never eaten so badly. 
Bread with dips ordered for 7,large fish plate for 44(€)!get after a long wait. On the map directly below each other. Be a misunderstanding, you can easily slip in the line.

reviews.title: Waiting a very long time for order
reviews.text: Waited an hour for the order to be delivered. No excuses whatsoever while the terrace was not half full. Then lunch doesn't taste good anymore.

reviews.title: Delicious food!
reviews.text: At the last minute we could still go with 12 men family. What a nice meal we had. Impressed by serving for such a group. Every dish was equally delicious, beautifully made up and the waiters were aware that no glass remained empty. Here we come back!

reviews.title: kann man nur weiter empfehlen
reviews.text: We had a very pleasant evening. Very warm welcome, good service and good food. Restaurant located directly at the port of Harlingen.

reviews.title: Don't go!
reviews.text: Don't go: bad food, steak completely overcooked, vegetables greasy and overcooked. Had to adjust everything separately, very expensive. And then the service: besides arguing with each other, they were also very unfriendly when we had a complaint. We were snubbed.

reviews.title: Worth a detour
reviews.text: Very friendly and excellent cuisine in a dramatic environment in a lovely village. The hotel is tidy, clean and with excellent maintenance.

reviews.title: Sorry, but would not recommend
reviews.text:
Would not recommend. Owners don’t seem to care (or inspect) the rooms. Lamps were not working, towel racks missing, etc.
Additionally walls are paper thin. You can literally follow every conversation in neighboring rooms, in my case, the whole night long.
Breakfast was basic but ok.

reviews.title: Worst dinner you can get
reviews.text: Worst dinner ever. Completely overcooked tasteless mussels for a ridiculous price of 25 euro and we had to ask for bread which to runes out to be old and dried out and was charged at a ridiculous extra price. Never again

reviews.title: A memorable Lunch!
reviews.text:
We ate here on Saturday Lunchtime - It was not busy and we sat in the restaurant at the rear of the hotel with a splendid view of the old harbour with boats of all descriptions constantly on the move,
The food was the best we had tasted for a long time - the work of a chef on top of his game. Particular mention for the Bruschetta starter - 3 slices of toasted bread each with a different flavour, salmon, carpaccio beef and vegetarian.
If there was a class above 'Excellent' on Trip Advisor I would be tempted to award it.

reviews.title: Extra small portions
reviews.text: This is one of the few restaurants who offer a vegan option on their menu. Now, when I am paying 18 euros for a dish I expect to leave satisfied, not hungry. I ordered the sweet potato lasagna, which was super delicious, however they just gave me a miniature square piece of it. Good presentation, but too small and not worth the money. You can get a whole plate of real lasagna for those money at other restaurants on the island.The portions are a joke. The staff on the other hand is friendly and helpful.

reviews.title: Still the best for the "zeetong"
reviews.text:
We have been at this restaurant for many years as we lunch during our wait for the 15:00 ferry to West-Terschelling. 
The quality is staying at its highest level. It is one of the places in the Netherlands were you can still get a large size zeetong wel prepared and nicely served by true professionals.
We regret the diappearance of the Chablis from the wine-list though; it was marrying so well with the zeetong.
Consider using the free parking facilities....

reviews.title: Great setting
reviews.text: We hadn’t booked, but were shown to a table with a view of the canal and the comings and goings of a variety of boats. Service was prompt and pleasant. We were given small cups of complimentary soup, which was very tasty. We chose items from the specials menu, which cost less, but were nicely presented and well cooked. The ambience is pleasant,with very comfortable seating.

reviews.title: Business trip
reviews.text: Have stayed in this hotel several times for business . Always very good, rooms clean and nice choice of food on the menu. English menu version if required . Has fee paying  car park but limited in spaces, nice outside patio area overlooking canal for dinner or food.

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide
tripContent.description: "Our family loves going to Orlando—and not just for the theme parks. Yes, we enjoy getting to ride rollercoasters and be transported to another world, but spending time in a colorful, diverse city and the surrounding nature is delightful. We live just over an hour from Orlando, so when we feel the need for good city vibes and to feel welcome in a neighborhood besides our own, Orlando is a fantastic option for us." - Rob Taylor, 2TravelDads.com

seoInfo.metaDescription: Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.
Here are more than a dozen places to paddle, cast a line, and raise your mainsail.
It’s a privilege to visit the world’s most beautiful oceans. Celebrate World Oceans Day by learning how to protect them.

reviews.title: One of the few open places on a November-Monday evening. Friendly service, even for late arrivals.
reviews.text: Restaurant; Food was fine, service was friendly, price tags are rather high but the restaurant is above average in general so what you get is overall priced OK.

reviews.title: Only had breakfast here
reviews.text: Breakfasted here twice whilst staying the adjacent boutique hotel. The average rating reflects the fact that "Good" is not an option.

reviews.title: Excellent kitchen
reviews.text:
Excellent breakfastbuffet and many choiches for a quality lunch or dinner. Or onlu have a drink. Very friendly staff. You can also eat outside on the terrace, with a nice view on the Waddenzee.
Shops are nearby

reviews.title: Outstanding stay
reviews.text: Very well located,special room #105 with balcony and a beautiful view of the harbour,great service and special attention from Postma family.When the weather permits great view at the terrace where you can enjoy an incredible sunset.TOP!

reviews.title: Good food and great view
reviews.text: We had lunch on a busy day and despite the crowds had good service and enjoyed our mussels. The portions of chips seemed small but we weren't charged for the additional chips we requested.

reviews.title: Fantastic Location
reviews.text: Come to Harlingen, the tall ship seaport in North Holland and enjoy a wonderful meal where you can relax and view the ships. The wine selection is superb and the staff are friendly and willing to accommodate. The dinner was "presentation" plus and said everything about the taste...particularly the sea bass. The portions were just the right size to leave "room for dessert". We highly recommend this classy place.

reviews.title: Prima restaurant, grote sortering verse vis
reviews.text:
Harlingen as a small authentic coastal town and one of the only pleasure harbors in the Netherlands without a lock has a nice restaurant directly located at the bridge with the entrance to the harbor which gives besides the food a nice view on all the pleasure vessels entering the harbor.

The restaurant has a good choice of fresh fish of a vey good quality. However if you want there is also a good choice of meat oriented dishes. We were with a group of 10 people with choices of various fish. We were all very happy and the french fried and salads were also of the same high quality. 

The cheese plate a bit boring. The choice of ice creams very limited but tasty. The warm chocolate cake fantastic. Try it out and also a good idea to share one with the two of you. All in all very enjoyable. Parking can be done at he hotel parking place or close by, after 18.00 hours it is free before watch it there are very frequent checks .

reviews.title: Wonderful fish
reviews.text:
We decided to go here despite some mixed reviews on tripadvisor and iens but were not disappointed, not at all.
It was a cold Saturday evening in April so we started with soup. The celeriac soup was very tasty, my Harlingen fish soup was very good.
My wife's salmon pasta was ok but my sea bass (prepared in the oven under a crust of salt) was delicious. I can't rave enough about that dish. The condiments were rather simple and underwhelming (baked potatoes and a simple salad) but who cares if you are served that sea bass.......
Little chocolate lava cake for dessert was very nice too.

reviews.title: Gastronomy when waiting for the 15:00 ferry to Terschelling
reviews.text:
The chef in this restaurant knows his craft. Food is excellent, from snacks to full size meals. The best dish is the sea sole that they have fresh at all times. The 500g affair is cooked to perfection and the taste of the delicate fish is to die for. It is not easy nowadays to find a restaurant serving this kind of dish. The day price of the sole was 42 EUR though so be prepared!
The view on the harbor is delightful and the arrival of the ferry from the waddenzee can be witnessed in detail.
There is a private free parking for the guests; use it and avoid the parking ticket or penalty (the Harlingen police will chase you!).

reviews.title: Tip: Fruit de Mer royal
reviews.text: I recommend the fruit de Mer Royal. What a meal. The service was very good and you have a nice view on the port.

reviews.title: To be Missed
reviews.text: Dreadful food, mediocre service and over priced.

reviews.title: food
reviews.text: Great menu, great presentation, taste wise excellent, the fish? so fresh!!!
